\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\section*\{Motivations for Piracy\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\subsection*\{Convenience -- Piracy is a service problem\}}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{Perceiving piracy as a competitive business is my preferred approach to reducing piracy. Understandably it is difficult to compete with a third-party offering a free product, though that doesn't mean that publishers can't consider their approach to content delivery to their paying customers.\}\\\\}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{The best example of this that I know of is the popular digital video game marketplace Steam. Steam is a dominating force in digital distribution on the PC platform (Windows, macOS and GNU/Linux). The PC platform is itself an open platform that anyone can create video games for without requiring approval from any single company...\}\\\\}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{Gabe Newell is the founder and CEO of Valve Software who are notable as the developer and publisher of the acclaimed Half-Life and CounterStrike series. His view on piracy is notable when interviewed about Steam's success in the Russia, a country that is known for widespread piracy.\}\\\\}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93One thing that we have learned is that piracy is not a pricing issue. It\u8217\'92s a service issue. The easiest way to stop piracy is not by putting antipiracy technology to work. It\u8217\'92s by giving those people a service that\u8217\'92s better than what they\u8217\'92re receiving from the pirates. For example, Russia. You say, oh, we\u8217\'92re going to enter Russia, people say, you\u8217\'92re doomed, they\u8217\'92ll pirate everything in Russia. Russia now outside of Germany is our largest continental European market.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ---Gabe Newell, founder and CEO of Valve Software (Geekwire, 2011)}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{In my experience I have had Amazon Prime Video reject me from playing back a movie because the HDMI cable I was using apparently didn't support the HDCP (High Definition Content Protection) standard.\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
