\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\section*\{Anti-Piracy Law\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{\\textbf\{Disclaimer:\} I am not a lawyer, certainly not a copyright lawyer. Therefore this section will be particularly light. I do want to provide a summary of notable legislation and its impact worldwide.\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\subsubsection*\{SOPA, PIPA and ACTA\}}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 %Heavy-handed legal bills SOPA, ACTA, PIPA}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{Legal attempts to further prevent internet copyright infringement outside of the current DMCA have a reputation for being very heavy-handed. There has been a concerted effort back in 2011 for the United States government to propose bills that target websites that host content (such as images, videos and music), there were known as the Stop Online Piracy Act (SOPA) and Protect Intellectual Property Act (PIPA).\}}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 %Lamar Smith}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \\noindent\{\\textit\{\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93...It's the SOPA cabana, it's the SOPA, SOPA can ban ya...\u8221\'94\}\}}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 ---Dan Bull\\\\}
